         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W. ¶ London ¶ June 1876 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ During a short visit I lately paid to Paris ¶ Bentham was in Paris from 2 to 10 June1876. On 5 June,he took his seat asmembre corresponda...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">76.06.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Library, Royal Botanic Gardens<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pencilled at top of letter in M's hand: '[Ba]tis, Halorageae Plantagineae (Myriceae Schnizlein)'.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="formtext" style="color: #2F5496; ">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">June 1876</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>During a short visit I lately paid to Paris<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham was in Paris from 2 to 10 June<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1876. On 5 June,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he took his seat as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">membre correspondant</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at the Académie des Sciences. See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Jackson (1906),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>pp. 236-7.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a second box of your Monocotyledons was I am informed sent off to you from Kew and the bill of lading duly forwarded to you by post.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bill of lading not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I trust you will have received it safely</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since my return I have done the Aroideae. I have ascertained that the leaves which Brown mistook for those of Dracontium<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R. Brown (1810), p. 337; see comments in Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6, p. 155.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>belong to the Brachyspatha variabilis which is Schultz's n. 562 from Port Darwin<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Frederick Schultze collected around Darwin,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1869-70.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— the leaf in your herbarium which you thought might be Brown's plant is I think that of Tacca pinnatifida — The leaves of Dracontium and Brachyspatha are so much alike as to be distinguishable only by a close examination of the venation</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have some difficulty in identifying some of Brown's Monocotyledons from his not having always revised his labels after the publication of the Prodromus<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>R.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Brown (1810).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but with some study I think I clear them up pretty well. Several of his Eriocaulons are neither in your collection nor in that of Kew<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Australian collections of Robert Brown (1773-1858) were at the British Museum.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have a few small families to finish up and in a few days hope to attack the Restiaceae</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the box sent you will find a copy of the new part of Genera Plantarum<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83). Part 2 of vol. 2 was published in May 1876 (TL2).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I hope some Australian botanists may order the work which is a heavy expense to us</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I trust that by the time you receive this you will have kindly sent off the Cyperaceae and Gramineae for which I hope to be ready in the course of September</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron F. v. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Aroideae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Brachyspatha variabilis</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cyperaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dracontium</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Eriocaulon</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Gramineae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Restiaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Tacca pinnatifida</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
